The paper discusses a technique for extracting and organizing knowledge from unstructured text corpus, which is a common problem in natural language processing and information retrieval. The proposed approach involves probabilistic topic modeling and concept hierarchy learning, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves linguistic processing and semantic analysis, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with organizing knowledge in a structured manner, which is relevant to sub-category cs.DB (Databases).
